 the [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]].\n*B{{anchor|endnote_B}}'''[[#ref B|^]]''' '''Won''' an [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]].\n*C{{anchor|endnote_C}}'''[[#ref C|^]]''' Produced by [[Robert Louis Buchanan|Robert Buchanan]].\n*D{{anchor|endnote_D}}'''[[#ref D|^]]''' New song integrated into the film for the 2001 Special Edition IMAX re-issue and 2001 DVD release.\n*E{{anchor|endnote_E}}'''[[#ref E|^]]''' Integrated into the film's end credits for the 2001 Special Edition IMAX re-issue and 2001 DVD release. On initial pressings of the original release of the soundtrack, this cue replaced the version used in the film up until the moment when the transformation begins. Eventually the album was re-pressed with the film version of the cue and has been presented in its proper film version on the 2001 and 2010 reissues.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1991\u20132017)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|14|artist=Soundtrack|album=Beauty and the Beast|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland2|28|artist=Soundtrack|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|25|artist=Soundtrack|album=Beauty and the Beast|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|New Zealand|21|artist=Soundtrack|album=Beauty and the Beast|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Spain|95|artist=Soundtrack|album=Beauty and the Beast|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|19|artist=Soundtrack|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardSoundtrack|9|artist=Soundtrack|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Canada|type=album|title=The Beauty and the Beast Soundtrack|artist=Various artists|award=Platinum|cert